sequenceDiagram
    participant FE as Frontend
    participant DC as DomainController
    participant DG as DomainDataGenerator
    participant BC as BatchController
    participant BJS as BatchJobService
    participant JL as JobLauncher
    participant JOB as bankingFileGenerationJob
    participant IR as DomainEntityItemReader
    participant IP as FileGenerationItemProcessor
    participant SR as StrategyResolver
    participant ST as FileGenerationStrategy
    participant IW as FileOutputItemWriter
    participant BML as BatchMetricsListener
    participant DB as H2 Database
    participant FS as output/ (filesystem)

    Note over FE,DG: Step 1 — seed sample data (LOW or HIGH load profile)
    FE->>DC: POST /api/domain/generate?loadProfile=LOW|HIGH
    DC->>DG: generate(LoadProfile)
    DG->>DB: save accounts + transactions + statements
    DG-->>DC: GenerationResult
    DC-->>FE: GenerateDomainResponse

    Note over FE,FS: Step 2 — trigger a Spring Batch job per (fileType × library)
    FE->>BC: POST /api/batch/generate {fileType, library}
    BC->>BJS: launch(fileType, library)
    BJS->>JL: run(job, params)
    JL->>JOB: execute()
    JOB->>BML: beforeJob()
    loop chunks of 100
        JOB->>IR: read() → Transaction
        IR->>DB: findAll transactions
        JOB->>IP: process(transaction)
        IP->>SR: resolve(fileType, library)
        SR-->>IP: FileGenerationStrategy
        IP->>ST: generate([transaction], accounts)
        ST-->>IP: formatted string
        JOB->>IW: write(chunk)
    end
    IW->>FS: write output file
    IW->>JOB: afterStep() → COMPLETED
    JOB->>BML: afterJob()
    BML->>DB: save BenchmarkMetrics
    JOB-->>BJS: JobExecution
    BJS-->>BC: BatchJobResult
    BC-->>FE: BatchJobResponse {fileContent, fileName, status}
